"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-New-Sports-Greater-Olympics-Flag-football-s-appeal-surges-in-China-1vTYoh20V5C-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Li Fanfei is at the forefront of the flag football movement in China, shining as the quarterback of the Contenders, a national champion team\\u00a0from Beijing. Beyond his role on the field, Li is also the head coach for flag football at the Ambassion Club, a vibrant sports community that promotes an exciting urban sports lifestyle among the youth. Flag football is officially one of five new sports added to the Olympic program for the 2028 Summer Games in Los Angeles.  Li says he is thrilled to see the sport gaining\\u00a0increasing popularity\\u00a0and thrilling new opportunities in China.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"